From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: mt7921u-ai <patch-engineer@mt7921u.local>
Date: Fri, 2 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/6] wifi: mt76: mt7921u: add MCU command retry on USB

The USB mcu_ops does not set .max_retry (defaults to 0). When an MCU
command times out on USB, mt7921_mcu_parse_response() immediately
calls mt792x_reset(mdev), triggering a full chip reset for any
transient USB delay.

USB is inherently less reliable than PCIe: transient delays can be
caused by autosuspend transitions, bus contention, host controller
scheduling, cable issues, or firmware garbage collection pauses. A
single missed response should not require a full chip reset.

The mt76 core MCU layer already supports command retry via the
.max_retry field in struct mt76_mcu_ops. When a command times out
and max_retry > 0, the core resends the command up to max_retry
times before calling mcu_parse_response(). Only after all retries
are exhausted does the parse_response callback fire — and only then
does mt792x_reset() get called.

Set .max_retry = 3 for the USB mcu_ops. This is consistent with the
SDIO driver which also sets max_retry for its bus-specific
characteristics.

Fixes: 967a4ff41e4e ("mt76: mt7921: introduce mt7921u support")
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: mt7921u-ai <patch-engineer@mt7921u.local>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/usb.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/usb.c b/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/usb.c
index 1234567..abcdef3 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/usb.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/usb.c
@@ -65,6 +65,7 @@ static int mt7921u_mcu_init(struct mt792x_dev *dev)
 {
 	static const struct mt76_mcu_ops mcu_ops = {
+		.max_retry = 3,
 		.headroom = MT_SDIO_HDR_SIZE +
 			    sizeof(struct mt76_connac2_mcu_txd),
 		.tailroom = MT_USB_TAIL_SIZE,

